Larry: Before we update the quote, I would like to confirm that the version 14 upgrade will be completed before this project is implemented. Also, that they are okay with having new panels.
The team concurred that they will be on V14 by the time the project starts. The team would like to compare quoting new cabinets verses using the existing. There is not as much lead time on cabinets, so we can order a little later.
Larry: Also, I have a suggestion that they use Isolated CHARMs for the discrete inputs. The BOM currently has Dry Contact CHARMs. The isolated CHARMs can be set up as dry contact, but also work for inputs where the input power is field sourced.
Jeffrey said Isolated CHARMs would be fine with him.
Larry will work to get a quote on Friday or Monday. Larry should coordinate the site visit on April 5th with Jorge.

Larry Frechin - Hardware Design Vigen Biglar - Account Manager Greg Richter - Project Engineer - DeltaV/PLC Jorge - Implementation DeltaV/Project Manager Jeff Potter - Implementation DeltaV Bryan Daume - Luis
Danaus machine arriving with it's own Rockwell based MCC. Our job is to determine how to bring the data in. We would like to take a phased approach at integrating with the machine. Need to look at connection points and how to distribute the IO. The machine is part of a larger project. This is one of the largest projects for the next couple of years.
September 1st week start commissioning Last week of August should have everything to go We need to identify the hardware upfront to get it on order.
There are existing cabinets that they would like to put DeltaV hardware into. They are old Provox cabinets. During the visit we need to get an update on the list of instruments. There are still changes happening.
Put everyone in the status meeting Every 2 weeks status report to the same group.
Larry will have questions early next week after looking through the documents.
